content:
@Bryn Rhodes
Per the spec: 

For partial date/time values, the comparison is performed to the highest precision specified in both values.

Does this mean that @2019 = @2019-01 = @2019-01-01 = @2019-01-01T00:00:00 = @2019-01-01T00:00:00.000 = @2019-01-01T00:00:00.000Z ?
No, when the partials are specified to different levels of precision, the result is empty ({ }).
